# Tailwind CSS Styling Standards

## General Guidelines

- Use Tailwind CSS v4 as configured in [package.json](mdc:package.json)
- Prefer utility classes over custom CSS
- Use semantic class names and maintain consistency across components

## Design System

- Use the established color palette: blue-50 to indigo-100 for light mode, gray-900 to gray-800 for dark mode
- Implement responsive design using Tailwind's responsive prefixes
- Use consistent spacing with Tailwind's spacing scale
- Maintain accessibility with proper contrast ratios

## Component Styling Patterns

- Use gradient backgrounds for visual appeal (bg-gradient-to-br)
- Implement proper dark mode support with dark: prefixes
- Use container classes for consistent max-widths
- Apply proper padding and margins for spacing

## Layout Patterns

- Use flexbox and grid utilities for layout
- Implement proper responsive breakpoints
- Use max-w-* classes for content width constraints
- Apply proper centering with flex utilities

## Accessibility

- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper focus states
- Maintain keyboard navigation support

## Performance

- Avoid excessive utility class combinations
- Use Tailwind's built-in optimizations
- Minimize custom CSS in favor of utility classes
